[ANALYSIS]
The experiment `bow_20260514_181530_run_01` using a Bag of Words (BoW) architecture achieved a moderate F1 score of 0.7255 and an accuracy of 0.79, indicating that the model performed reasonably well on the validation set. The use of TF-IDF vectorization with a maximum of 10,000 features and considering up to bigrams (ngram_max=2) contributed positively to the results. However, the experiment did not explore different hyperparameters such as varying the logistic regression regularization strength (`logreg_c`) or adjusting the minimum document frequency (`min_df`), which could potentially improve performance further. For the next run, it would be beneficial to conduct a grid search over these hyperparameters and possibly increase the number of features to capture more nuanced patterns in the data. Additionally, experimenting with different vectorization techniques like word embeddings might yield better results if the BoW model is not fully capturing the semantic relationships between words.